  <processinfo id="aspace_7c39659618996b85ebb11fafd6b9f47e">
    <head>Processing Information</head>
<p>Minimally processed to the collection level in 2011. Description was augmented in 2018, and at this time materials were rehoused. In November 2023, accession 1977.568 was found to consist of photostat copies of material from this collection and was incorporated into it.</p>  </processinfo>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_459fff3c8809c5fdd8bd50dacfa49341">
    <head>Related Materials</head>
<p>Center for Brooklyn History holds the following related collections:</p><p>- Brookhaven deeds (1978.054)</p><p>- Purcell Robertson papers (1985.034)</p><p>- Smith families papers (ARC.244)</p><p>- Brooklyn and Long Island deeds collection (1978.006)</p><p>- Nathaniel R. Howell Suffolk County, Nassau County, and Queens County deeds collection (1977.243)</p>  </relatedmaterial>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_51403ac9c4572ffdc4abed2767399dab">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection documents early Colonial property transactions in the Long Island towns of Brookhaven and Southold. Materials include deeds, indentures, patents and warrents, and involve the Unkechaug Native Americans and English colonial administrator Edmund Andros.</p>  </scopecontent>
